# LICENSES.allowlist
#
# Allowed open-source license types for NuGet transitive dependencies.
# Enforced by the `license-compliance` CI job in `.github/workflows/ci.yml`
# (uses `nuget-license --allowed-license-types`).
#
# Format: one SPDX license identifier per line, sorted alphabetically.
# Blank lines and `#`-prefixed comments are ignored — comments must be
# stripped before passing this file to the tool (see the CI job).
#
# How to add a license:
#   1. Confirm the license is permissive enough for our SaaS distribution
#      model (no strong copyleft; no field-of-use restrictions).
#   2. Cross-check with legal if in doubt (anything not on this list
#      already required a one-time decision).
#   3. Add the SPDX identifier in alphabetical order with a one-line
#      comment explaining which package introduced the need.
#   4. The same PR must include the dependency upgrade or addition that
#      pulled in the new license — never expand the allowlist
#      speculatively.
#
# Baseline rationale (initial set): standard .NET 10 + EF Core 10 + AWS
# SDK + JWT stack. Microsoft and .NET Foundation packages ship under
# MIT; older Microsoft packages occasionally surface MS-PL. AWS SDK is
# Apache-2.0. Npgsql is PostgreSQL license. A handful of utility
# libraries (Newtonsoft.Json forks, etc.) use BSD-3-Clause.
Apache-2.0
BSD-2-Clause
BSD-3-Clause
MIT
MS-PL
PostgreSQL
